 Bolt CLOSED POSITION Without a properly working safety reversal system persons particularly small children could be SERIOUSLY INJURED or KILLED by a closing garage door.";i:35;s:84:"The gap between the bottom of the garage door and the floor MUST NOT exceed 14 6 mm.";i:36;s:22:"Garage door is closed.";i:37;s:80:"Safety Reversing Sensor Gap between floor and bottom of door must not exceed 14.";i:38;s:277:"Header Wall Access Door Closed Position Cable Pulley Bracket Header Bracket Trolley Straight Door Arm Emergency Release Rope Handle Door Bracket Curved Door Arm Header Wall Cable T-rail Garage Door 5 Access Door Floor must be level across width of door Safety Reversing Sensor.";i:39;s:177:"Most garage door openers feature a carriage that runs on a rail or along a tube from a motor to the front of the garage and an arm that connects the carriage to the garage door.";i:40;s:133:"While popular chain drive garage door openers connect the motor to the carriage with a chain other openers work slightly differently.";i:41;s:36:"In direct drive garage door openers.";i:42;s:69:"Use a wood screw or nail to hold locks in the open unlocked position.";i:43;s:75:"Operation at other than 230V50 Hz will cause opener malfunction and damage.";i:44;s:44:"To prevent possible SERIOUS INJURY OR DEATH.";i:45;s:101:"Always call for professional BD garage door service if garage door binds sticks or is out of balance.";i:46;s:97:"To avoid installation difﬁ culties do not run the garage door opener until instructed to do so.";i:47;s:52:"The front rail has a cut out window at the door end.";i:48;s:44:"The front and back rail both have rail tabs.";i:49;s:58:"These rail tabs MUST be on top of the rail when assembled.";i:50;s:29:"Remove the straight door arm.";i:51;s:113:"5-2 Install the straight door armcurved door arm 5-3 Position and secure the chain for a multi-part rail WARNING.";i:52;s:63:"To avoid possible serious injury to fingers from moving garage.";i:53;s:44:"6-4 Position the garage door opener CAUTION.";i:54;s:61:"To prevent damage to garage door with help of another person.";i:55;s:232:"CLOSED POSITION Garage Door Spring Garage Door Door Bracket Curved Door Arm Header Bracket Gap between ﬂ oor and bottom of door must not exceed 14 6 mm Torsion Spring OR Access Door Safety Reversing Sensor Safety Reversing Sensor.";i:56;s:59:"Garage door openers use a motor to open and close the door.";i:57;s:76:"The motor turns a belt or chain which is connected to a trolley or carriage.";i:58;s:71:"This trolley then pushes on the opener arm moving the door up and down.";i:59;s:56:"A piece of rope usually red hangs down from the trolley.";}}